Create a mystical student dashboard for "The Empirical Academy," a 13th-century inspired magical institution where scholars study natural philosophy through the Three Virtues: Thoth (wisdom/moon/blue), Ma'at (balance/scales/silver), and Caerus (timing/opportunity/gold). The aesthetic is "celestial night meets illuminated manuscript" — imagine studying by candlelight in an ancient observatory, with deep purples and midnight blues, twinkling starfields, ornate golden borders, and glowing progress indicators. Typography evokes medieval manuscripts with decorative headers and elegant serif body text. The interface feels like a living grimoire crossed with an RPG character sheet: students track their advancement through virtue ranks, log magical workings and study notes, monitor moon phases for optimal timing, manage their collection of physical tools (herbs, crystals, ritual items), and watch their experience bars fill as they progress from Apprentice to Journeyman to Master. Every element reinforces the fantasy of being enrolled in a secret academy of empirical magic, where knowledge is accumulated through observation, balance is maintained through ethical practice, and success depends on perfect timing — all tracked in a beautifully designed scholarly interface that glows with arcane energy.